originalText.text:
I thought I was being responsible and I reserved a spot with ParkWiz or Best park app.  The app charged me $31
From 7PM to 7PM, so we thought we were all set.
What I didn’t expect was the garage charging me $30.  Twice !!!!!
Grand total for 3 hours $92.
On top of that, they were incredibly rude and insisted I had an oversized vehicle.
Ford Flex ? Is a Car!!! and this is stealing.
Never again. Stay away. Crooks

originalText.text: Bunch of crooks. If you are staying FairField Inn, they will ask when you will be the last day. Don't tell them when. On the first day, I took my car out after 3 hours for dinner, they charged me $15 or so. On the last day, after overnight parking, I re-parked my car in the morning after breakfast. After 2 1/2 hours for check out of the hotel, they charged me a new $50 or so. So, I had to pay double on the last day. I asked them many times if that is after the discount from the hotel stay. They knew we are the tourists and decided to s**t us up on the last day. Just bunch of crooks.

originalText.text: Don’t park here if you care about your car and yourself. While I do lost the parking ticket, there are many other ways to prove the car is mine. However, they try to copy my registration, insurance, and driver license. I believe even the police have no such right. I can’t image what they would do to me if they got my informations. BTW, some of there staff are so rude.
